The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	Ramabai Nagar, Sept. 25 (PTI): At least 42 people have died of viral fever, malaria and dengue in more than 82 villages in Kanpur district of Uttar Pradesh in the past one month.           
	Of the 82 villages affected by the water-borne diseases, 42 are badly hit, district magistrate Saroj Tiwari said. However, all measures are being taken to control the spread of the diseases and medical staff have been sent to the affected villages, he added.                  
	Mumbai (PTI): PepsiCo and Coca-Cola have filed a petition in Bombay High Court challenging a three-fold octroi charged by a municipal authority on their products. PepsiCo has been asked to pay Rs 24.63 lakh while Coke has been charged Rs 1.08 crore.                  
	Mumbai (PTI): An aide of gangster Abu Salem has been allegedly attacked by four inmates inside Arthur Road Jail, two months after the underworld don was assaulted in the high-security prison. Mohammed Mehndi Hassan suffered injuries on his face and hand.                   
	Mumbai (PTI): A court has allowed the income tax department to auction a flat of Bhupen Dalal, an accused in the 1992 securities scam, to compensate his tax dues.                                                                                                                                              
